# ============================================================================
# §Doc-only — seal-cap rejection error name (Sealed — four-state/merge-outcome pass)
# ============================================================================
# The seal-cap rejection is Sealed (an INERT below-seal parent that changes
# nothing: parent.serial < seal_serial) — renamed from SiblingLocked (and earlier
# ParentLocked) at the four-state / formalized-merge-outcome pass. Not every
# below-seal parent is Sealed: a parent AT the seal (parent_serial == seal_serial)
# extends cleanly, and a sibling at the seal's own serial (parent v_{seal-1},
# parent_serial == seal_serial - 1) forms a live fork (Forked / Disputed),
# retained — not Sealed. The cap bounds content extended FROM the seal; Sealed is
# the inert below-seal parent — not a "locked parent," and not a sibling to the seal.

# ============================================================================
# §Doc-only — KEL reshape: data-local detection + the manifest/spine model
# ============================================================================
# The KEL primitive docs reconciled to the post-reshape canon (event-shape +
# protocol-doctrine): divergence detection is data-local (the verifier walks
# retained branches; the witness beacon propagates, never decides), so the
# federation-decides framing and its vocabulary are retired:
#   federation-irreconcilable  — the federation does not pronounce a verdict;
#     a fork with >= 2 sealed branches reads "disputed" by a data-local walk;
#   effective-SAID synthetics divergent:{prefix} / irreconcilable:{prefix} — the
#     truly-dead kels synthetics stay banned. vdti's first-seen effective-SAID is:
#     a single confirmed tip → its real SAID; NO single tip → a type-tagged
#     `synthetic` marker recoupled to the verdict (forked: / disputed:), qualified
#     by prefix + position, NOT a digest over the competing tips (adversarially
#     extensible → flood-unstable, deleted). So the verdict-recoupled colon forms
#     forked: / disputed: are LIVE (the synthetic value on a no-single-tip chain);
#     bare "divergent" / "irreconcilable" and the "forked"/"disputed" verdict words
#     stay live too — only the kels divergent: / irreconcilable: colon forms are dead;
#   policy_satisfied  — the verifier token reports the structural-validity
#     result, not a policy signal (authorization is structural; the acceptance
#     policy is the relying party's, at the document/application layer);
#   RecoveryRecord  — a repair commits a losing branch's root as the `fork`
#     manifest role, not a separate audit-row type;
#   witnessParams / witnessThreshold / witnessSelectionSize  — the witness
#     config rides the `witnesses` manifest role as a { threshold, signers } SAD.
federation-irreconcilable
divergent:\{prefix\}
irreconcilable:\{prefix\}
\bpolicy_satisfied\b
\bRecoveryRecord\b
\bwitnessParams\b

