# ============================================================================
# §Doc-only — root-pointing repair model (the fork role = a root, not a tip)
# ============================================================================
# A repair's fork names a losing branch's ROOT — its first divergent event,
# condemning the whole subtree (growth-proof) — never its tip. The tip-pointing
# model and its apparatus (a re-freeze on an under-covering repair; a follow-up
# repair required to catch post-repair growth) are retired: an unnamed-content
# repair is ACCEPTED (unnamed content inerts below the seal, growth dead
# on ascent). Bare "tip" stays live everywhere (chain tip, branch tip, the
# SEL's IEL-anchored tip); only the fork-role collocations and the retired
# apparatus regress.
archived[- ]branch tips?
`forks` tips
re-frozen

